01:19.000 --> 01:21.321
- Now it
had become the still center

01:21.440 --> 01:25.729
of that spinning wheel
of misfortune.

01:25.840 --> 01:27.524
The world turned
round him,

01:27.640 --> 01:32.043
leaving him
miraculously untouched.

01:32.160 --> 01:35.482
The croupier had
reached his goal.

01:35.600 --> 01:38.968
He no longer heard
the sound of the ball.

01:43.160 --> 01:45.766
To begin with,
he was Jack Manfred.

01:47.320 --> 01:49.641
- Now, then.
- I want a job, Giles.

01:49.760 --> 01:52.047
- I see. Well...

01:52.160 --> 01:55.403
Let me tell you a little bit
about our operation.

01:55.520 --> 01:57.409
We like
personality authors.

01:57.520 --> 01:59.443
People the public
recognizes.

01:59.560 --> 02:01.767
Celebrity's what
sells books.

02:01.880 --> 02:03.928
You can always find somebody
to do the writing.

02:04.040 --> 02:07.567
What we need is the face...
then the concept.

02:07.680 --> 02:11.048
Right now I'm looking
for a soccer novel.

02:11.160 --> 02:14.881
Something where a tycoon
buys a lousy team

02:15.000 --> 02:16.445
and takes it to the top.

02:16.560 --> 02:17.846
Seven-figure
transfer fees.

02:17.960 --> 02:20.440
Corruption all
down the line.

02:20.560 --> 02:23.086
Violence on
and off the pitch.

02:23.200 --> 02:25.441
Steroids.

02:27.520 --> 02:30.171
You got any concepts?

02:30.280 --> 02:34.080
It could be a thug story.

02:34.200 --> 02:37.647
I'll tell you what,
why don't you think about it?

02:37.800 --> 02:40.167
Hmm? Couple of pages.

02:42.280 --> 02:44.408
With plenty of sex,
of course.

02:44.560 --> 02:46.562
Fiona!

02:47.880 --> 02:49.962
- Interesting, Giles.

02:50.080 --> 02:53.448
I will think about it.

02:53.560 --> 02:56.086
- Let me give you three
words of advice, Jack.

02:56.200 --> 02:58.043
Don't give up.

02:58.160 --> 02:59.844
Stick with it.

02:59.960 --> 03:02.964
Who persists, wins,
that's my motto.

03:03.120 --> 03:05.600
Write, write, write.

03:05.720 --> 03:08.485
- And Jack had
three words for Giles.

03:08.600 --> 03:10.807
Go fuck yourself.

03:33.680 --> 03:36.160
Jack knew something
was wrong.

03:36.320 --> 03:39.961
He'd forgotten Giles' advice.
Giles said three words.

03:49.440 --> 03:52.125
Nobody around, leave a
message after the beep.

03:56.440 --> 03:57.965
- Jacko.

03:58.080 --> 04:00.128
If you're there,
pick up, would ya.

04:00.240 --> 04:03.369
I want to talk to
you, it's important.

04:03.480 --> 04:06.051
Jacko, I've got
some news for you.

04:06.160 --> 04:08.686
Come on, Jacko.

04:08.800 --> 04:10.370
- Yeah, Dad, it's me.

04:10.520 --> 04:12.807
- How's it going?
- Good, yeah.

04:12.920 --> 04:16.129
- Found a job yet?
- No.

04:16.240 --> 04:19.369
- Well I've got something
for you, in London I mean.

04:19.480 --> 04:21.447
I've been chatting with
some friends. Now...

04:21.560 --> 04:24.291
Do you know
the Golden Lion Casino?

04:24.400 --> 04:25.970
They're looking
for a dealer.

04:26.120 --> 04:29.363
- Yeah, that's not
what I wanna do, Dad.

04:29.480 --> 04:31.403
- Now, I know you don't
like taking my advice...

04:31.520 --> 04:33.090
- No, it's not that.

04:33.200 --> 04:36.170
- Listen, I've set
this up for you.

04:36.280 --> 04:38.851
Now you call the Golden Lion,
and you ask to speak

04:38.960 --> 04:41.691
to Mr. Reynolds.
That's the manager.

04:41.840 --> 04:44.923
Now I don't know him personally,
but I have spoken to his boss.

04:45.040 --> 04:47.281
Now, don't say no, Jacko.

04:47.400 --> 04:49.971
Give yourself a break.

04:50.080 --> 04:52.651
- All right, Dad. Yeah,
I'll think about it.

04:52.760 --> 04:55.161
- Reynolds at
the Golden Lion.

04:55.280 --> 04:57.965
- Yeah. All right, Dad.
- Yes. I'll call him.

04:58.080 --> 05:00.924
- You do that.
- That's my boy.

05:02.760 --> 05:04.524
- So how are
you doing, Dad?

05:04.640 --> 05:06.005
- Great.

05:06.160 --> 05:08.367
Yeah, just started
a new company.

05:08.480 --> 05:10.130
Solid financing.

05:10.240 --> 05:12.891
It's good.

05:13.040 --> 05:16.806
Jacko, you know I
love you, don't you?

05:16.960 --> 05:19.281
- Yeah. I know that.

05:19.400 --> 05:21.129
- Don't let
yourself down.

05:21.240 --> 05:22.844
- I won't.

05:22.960 --> 05:25.566
- I'll keep in touch.

05:28.080 --> 05:30.162
- Goodbye, Dad.

05:34.520 --> 05:37.251
- It was unbelievable.
- I was in the room.

05:37.360 --> 05:39.761
500.

05:39.880 --> 05:42.929
Uh-huh. Blackjack.

05:43.040 --> 05:45.725
See you then, bye.

05:45.840 --> 05:48.525
- Sorry to have kept you.
- What'll you have?

06:00.560 --> 06:04.201
- Nope. Jack knew
it still wasn't quite right.

06:13.200 --> 06:15.806
- I wanna fuck
the whole world over!

06:15.920 --> 06:17.843
Ha!

06:21.960 --> 06:25.362
- He had
just one word for Giles.

06:40.040 --> 06:43.362
- David Reynolds.
- I'm the manager.

06:43.480 --> 06:45.801
- Sit down, John.
- Jack.

06:47.320 --> 06:49.891
- You've been recommended
by the management here.

06:50.000 --> 06:52.207
They know your father.

06:52.320 --> 06:54.482
He's a bit of
a reputation, hasn't he?

06:54.640 --> 06:56.529
- Has he?

06:56.640 --> 06:57.766
- In any case, I understand
you've had some

06:57.880 --> 07:01.043
previous experience
in South Africa.

07:01.160 --> 07:04.687
You'll find the rules here
just a little bit different.

07:04.800 --> 07:06.450
Before we start, you haven't
got a police record, have you?

07:06.560 --> 07:08.528
- No.

07:08.640 --> 07:11.007
- What school did you go to?
- I was at Bedales.

07:11.120 --> 07:14.329
- Oh. I don't think
I know that one.

07:14.440 --> 07:16.761
Private, I suppose.

07:16.880 --> 07:19.360
There's three types
of casino in the UK.

07:19.480 --> 07:21.528
High volume, small action,
and middle of the road.

07:21.640 --> 07:23.642
That's us.
Okay, Charlie.

07:23.760 --> 07:25.046
- Do you have
a salon prive?

07:25.160 --> 07:27.845
- We tried.
- Wasn't enough business.

07:27.960 --> 07:31.009
- Punters like company.
- Welcome back, Jack...

07:32.280 --> 07:35.682
...to the house
of addiction.

07:35.800 --> 07:37.643
- Thanks, Charlie.

07:42.320 --> 07:44.607
Right. Let's see you
handle the chips.

07:44.720 --> 07:46.006
- I have to assume
the serial numbers

07:46.120 --> 07:48.282
on the bowl
and wheel correspond.

07:48.400 --> 07:52.041
- We check every two days.
- Why not every day?

07:52.200 --> 07:54.089
- Procedure here.

07:56.400 --> 07:58.482
Right, sort the chips.

08:01.480 --> 08:03.369
Go.

08:19.160 --> 08:21.049
Good.

08:23.680 --> 08:26.843
All right, now pay
me out $1,800 in 25s.

08:36.280 --> 08:39.284
Very good. Okay, let's have
a look at your blackjack.

08:52.040 --> 08:53.530
- Fourteen.

08:53.640 --> 08:57.247
Too many.

08:57.360 --> 08:58.964
Nineteen, Sixteen.

08:59.080 --> 09:02.084
Too many.

09:02.200 --> 09:03.804
Thirteen.

09:03.920 --> 09:05.684
Eighteen, Fourteen.

09:05.800 --> 09:06.801
Nineteen.

09:06.920 --> 09:08.809
Twenty.

09:12.120 --> 09:15.044
- What's the count?
- Minus nine.

09:15.200 --> 09:18.249
- I make it minus eight.
- Minus nine.

09:18.360 --> 09:21.443
- What makes you so sure?
- It's the rule.

09:21.560 --> 09:22.686
Always stand by
your first count.

09:22.800 --> 09:25.565
The odds are
you're right.

09:25.680 --> 09:27.808
- Good call.
- You want me to check?

09:27.960 --> 09:31.362
- I said,
good call.

09:31.480 --> 09:34.165
- lthadtaken
him 45 minutes,

09:34.280 --> 09:36.760
but Jack now had
Mr. Reynolds' number.

09:36.880 --> 09:38.405
The man
couldn't count.

09:38.520 --> 09:41.808
- Right, just let me
run through a few things.

09:41.920 --> 09:44.002
As a dealer,
you never gamble.

09:44.120 --> 09:47.124
Not anywhere. And we'll
need your picture.

09:47.240 --> 09:50.005
- What for?
- For the database.

09:50.120 --> 09:52.646
It can be accessed by
every casino in the country.

09:52.760 --> 09:54.046
We have the same
system for punters.

09:54.160 --> 09:56.049
- I don't gamble.
- Ever?

09:56.160 --> 09:59.448
- I don't gamble,
Mr. Reynolds.

09:59.560 --> 10:01.324
- Huh.

10:01.440 --> 10:03.522
- Next point.

10:03.640 --> 10:05.130
Friendships between
croupiers inside

10:05.240 --> 10:08.767
or outside the casino
are discouraged.

10:08.920 --> 10:11.651
Relationships with
females working here...

10:11.760 --> 10:13.808
- are expressly forbidden.
- We had the same rule

10:13.920 --> 10:16.400
in Sun City, but it was
impossible to check.

10:16.520 --> 10:18.682
- Well this isn't
South Africa.

10:18.800 --> 10:21.963
We'd know, because
someone would report it.

10:22.080 --> 10:23.570
Believe me, someone
always does.

10:23.680 --> 10:26.251
- Does know, or does report?
- What would happen

10:26.360 --> 10:28.522
if I knew something like that
and didn't report it?

10:28.640 --> 10:30.529
- We'd know.

10:30.640 --> 10:33.086
There are no secrets
in this casino.

10:33.200 --> 10:36.488
- And you'd be punished.
- How?

10:36.600 --> 10:39.729
- First offense, verbal warning.
- Second offense, written warning.

10:39.840 --> 10:42.923
That one's filed and sometimes
copied to the gaming board.

10:43.040 --> 10:45.566
My discretion.

10:45.680 --> 10:48.604
Third offense, you'd
be sacked on the spot.

10:48.720 --> 10:52.441
You'd never work in a casino
in this country again.

10:52.560 --> 10:54.562
And there's
another rule.

10:54.680 --> 10:57.923
You're forbidden to talk to
or recognize a punter

10:58.040 --> 11:01.089
outside the casino. If you see
someone who's gambled here,

11:01.200 --> 11:03.521
even if it's just
casually on the street,

11:03.680 --> 11:06.251
you must ignore
him or her.

11:07.560 --> 11:09.483
Not married, are you?

11:09.600 --> 11:11.568
Girlfriend?

11:11.680 --> 11:14.445
- Yeah.
- She's not in the...

11:14.560 --> 11:16.608
she's not in the gaming
business, is she?

11:16.720 --> 11:18.324
- No.

11:18.440 --> 11:21.205
- Good.

11:23.920 --> 11:27.083
This is our
Crow's nest.

11:27.200 --> 11:28.929
I'm showing you it now, but
you'll never see it again.

11:29.080 --> 11:31.048
- Very impressive.

11:32.920 --> 11:35.207
- We have tapes here
that go back six months.

11:35.320 --> 11:38.005
Here, let me show
you something.

11:46.480 --> 11:48.608
See that?

11:48.720 --> 11:50.882
Six weeks ago.

11:51.000 --> 11:54.083
Dealer missed it.
Guy up here missed it.

11:54.200 --> 11:56.362
I watch these
tapes after hours.

11:56.480 --> 11:58.767
Nothing gets by me.

11:58.880 --> 12:01.531
Lady's in jail now.

12:01.640 --> 12:04.484
It's easier to take ten
million pounds from a bank,

12:04.600 --> 12:07.410
than to take one
penny from this casino.

12:09.320 --> 12:12.847
Right. Well, as soon as you get
your license, you can start.

12:13.000 --> 12:14.286
- Fine.

12:14.400 --> 12:15.890
- So...

12:16.000 --> 12:19.129
Are you planning to make
a career in casino work?

12:19.240 --> 12:20.480
And end up like you?

12:20.600 --> 12:22.329
L-- I just
want a job.

12:22.440 --> 12:24.488
- You're not the usual
type we get in here, Jack.

12:24.600 --> 12:26.887
Mr. Reynolds
was right, it was true.

12:27.000 --> 12:28.764
Excuse me.

12:28.880 --> 12:30.723
- Jack was
up above the world.

12:30.840 --> 12:33.684
A writer looking
down on his subject.

12:33.800 --> 12:35.484
A detached...

12:35.600 --> 12:37.443
- I can't talk
about that just now.

12:37.560 --> 12:40.291
- Voyeur.
- I'm with somebody.

12:40.400 --> 12:43.609
Well, they can wait.

12:43.720 --> 12:46.291
I'll be home at
the usual time.

12:48.960 --> 12:51.042
Don't get married, Jack.

12:51.160 --> 12:54.642
Casino work doesn't mix
with house and garden.

12:54.760 --> 12:56.125
Any questions?

12:56.240 --> 12:58.891
- Yeah. What's the salary?

13:01.680 --> 13:04.889
- The casino paid
its staff monthly in arrears.

13:05.000 --> 13:08.482
He would have to wait six
weeks for his first check.

13:08.640 --> 13:10.961
- He needed money now.
- So, what kind of deal

13:11.080 --> 13:13.128
are you looking for?

13:13.240 --> 13:14.810
- What's the book price?

13:14.920 --> 13:16.649
- That's not relevant.

13:16.760 --> 13:20.446
Old car like this,
depends on the condition.

13:21.840 --> 13:23.968
- The car was
a gift from Jack's father.

13:24.080 --> 13:25.844
That's to say,
Jack Sr. Had given it to him

13:25.960 --> 13:29.043
before the
bailiffs arrived.

13:29.200 --> 13:32.921
- And this ain't exactly
what you call "mint."

13:33.080 --> 13:35.162
- How about $1,500?

13:35.280 --> 13:37.806
- How about $500?
- What?

13:37.960 --> 13:40.691
- How about we split
the difference?

13:40.840 --> 13:42.524
$750.

13:42.640 --> 13:44.927
- Is that your idea
of arithmetic?

13:45.040 --> 13:47.771
- I'm not a mathematician.
- I'm in business.

13:47.880 --> 13:50.486
- $850.
- $750.

13:54.160 --> 13:55.730
- He suddenly
wanted to be rid of it.

13:55.840 --> 13:59.083
Hang on tightly,
let go lightly.

14:06.880 --> 14:09.645
Jack imagined people
reading his book.

14:09.760 --> 14:12.001
One day he would get
into their heads.

14:12.160 --> 14:14.083
Play with their
imaginations.

14:14.200 --> 14:16.771
Test their feelings.

14:18.960 --> 14:22.203
He would tell them, you have
to make the choice in life.

14:22.320 --> 14:24.800
Be a gambler,
or a croupier.

14:26.880 --> 14:29.486
And then live with your
decision, come what may.

14:31.960 --> 14:34.691
Marion saw life
differently.

14:35.760 --> 14:38.764
She was a romantic...

14:38.880 --> 14:40.723
and thought
he was, too.

14:55.680 --> 14:57.887
- I couldn't resist them.

14:58.040 --> 15:00.407
- You mean I
won't resist them.

15:00.520 --> 15:02.170
- No.

15:02.280 --> 15:06.205
I'm not ready for you.

15:06.320 --> 15:08.482
There's some vodka
in the freezer.

15:08.600 --> 15:11.331
- You want me drunk?
- I won't take that long!

15:35.920 --> 15:37.763
Jack.

15:46.480 --> 15:48.323
- Wow.

15:51.760 --> 15:53.683
You really are
a beautiful woman.

15:53.800 --> 15:55.370
- It's not just
inner beauty, is it?

15:55.480 --> 15:57.482
- Turn around.

16:02.040 --> 16:04.042
You're all I desire.

16:15.760 --> 16:19.128
- Where did you get it?
- I sold the car.

16:19.240 --> 16:21.447
- You shouldn't have done that,
I know what it meant to you.

16:21.560 --> 16:23.528
- I owe you for the rent.

16:23.640 --> 16:26.120
It's only a car,
I can get another.

16:26.240 --> 16:27.730
- Take it back.
- No.

16:27.880 --> 16:31.089
- Till you sell your book.
- Marion, let's face the truth.

16:31.200 --> 16:33.089
Nobody is gonna publish it.

16:33.200 --> 16:37.205
- Of course, they are.
- You just have to be patient.

16:41.360 --> 16:43.089
- I'm betting on you.
- I'm not much of a bet.

16:43.200 --> 16:45.521
- You are to me.

16:48.920 --> 16:51.127
Come into
my world.

17:00.000 --> 17:02.241
You're my prisoner.

17:02.360 --> 17:04.203
- I've got something
to tell you.

17:04.319 --> 17:06.925
- I wanna hear it.
- I've got a job.

17:10.400 --> 17:13.165
- What job'?
- In a casino.

17:13.280 --> 17:16.887
As a croupier. Dealer.

17:17.000 --> 17:19.765
- How did you land that?
- It came my way.

17:19.880 --> 17:22.451
450 a week.

17:22.599 --> 17:25.046
<i>' 450'?</i>

17:25.160 --> 17:26.605
What did you do?
Just walk in and say,

17:26.720 --> 17:29.610
- I want to be a croupier?
- Don't you need training?

17:29.720 --> 17:32.883
- I had training.
- In the republic.

17:33.000 --> 17:35.526
- You were
a croupier there?

17:35.640 --> 17:37.722
You never
told me that.

17:37.840 --> 17:39.968
I thought you just
knew some gamblers.

17:40.120 --> 17:42.168
- I start Monday week.

17:42.280 --> 17:44.248
- 450 a week?

17:44.360 --> 17:46.840
I've never earned
that in my life.

17:49.040 --> 17:50.769
You're an enigma, you are.

17:50.920 --> 17:52.843
A fucking enigma.

17:52.960 --> 17:56.043
- I'm not an enigma.
- Just a contradiction.

17:56.160 --> 17:58.481
- You sold the car.

17:58.640 --> 18:01.610
You've got a job.

18:01.720 --> 18:04.007
What's the third thing?

18:06.880 --> 18:09.121
Tell me.

18:10.960 --> 18:14.043
- There's no third thing.

18:14.160 --> 18:16.527
Don't be superstitious.

18:18.800 --> 18:20.723
- I love you, Jack.
- You know that.

18:20.840 --> 18:24.481
- And he half-loved
Marion, and she knew that, too.

18:25.560 --> 18:27.642
You trying to
read my palm?

18:29.400 --> 18:32.563
- You've got such
beautiful hands.

18:32.680 --> 18:36.082
The hands of a
Conjurer, a woman told him once.

18:36.200 --> 18:38.282
Or a cardsharp.

18:41.560 --> 18:45.565
- Do you work around here?
- My office is in Shanghai.

18:45.680 --> 18:48.251
- What do you do?
- I'm an arms dealer.

18:49.760 --> 18:52.969
- So, what line
of work are you in, then?

18:54.600 --> 18:58.321
- I'm an undertaker.

18:58.440 --> 19:00.727
- Really?

19:08.600 --> 19:10.807
- Now place your bets, please.

19:18.960 --> 19:21.691
- Jack Manfred.
- Jack Manfred. Table three.

19:25.680 --> 19:28.570
- And you have a new
dealer. Thank you.

19:28.680 --> 19:30.523
Usual bunch.

19:30.640 --> 19:32.244
They didn't know Jack,
but he knew them.

19:32.400 --> 19:34.607
Good evening,
ladies and gentlemen.

19:37.200 --> 19:39.680
- Where's the other
fellow? Where's Jeff?

19:39.800 --> 19:40.722
- Where's Jeff'?
- Jeff.

19:40.840 --> 19:43.366
He's been
re-assigned, sir.

19:43.480 --> 19:45.369
- Well let's hope you know
how to do your job.

19:45.480 --> 19:49.166
- In fives.
- Change.

19:49.280 --> 19:52.124
- What aftershave are you using?
- Never converse

19:52.240 --> 19:54.811
with the punters.
Slows things down.

19:54.960 --> 19:57.361
Money down.

19:57.480 --> 19:59.881
Speed is volume.
Volume is profit for the casino.

20:00.000 --> 20:03.288
Aim at 4O spins an hour.
Place your bets, please.

20:13.440 --> 20:15.522
No more bets,
thank you.

20:18.200 --> 20:19.690
10 black.

20:42.040 --> 20:43.451
Ooh, the scam.

20:43.560 --> 20:45.961
Come in with three grand
cash, no questions asked.

20:46.080 --> 20:49.163
Launder it by getting a
casino check when you cash in.

20:49.280 --> 20:51.567
Jack wondered why
Mr. Reynolds permitted it.

20:51.680 --> 20:54.126
After all, there was no
profit in it for the casino.

20:54.240 --> 20:57.608
Place your
bets, please.

20:57.720 --> 20:59.961
Or was there?

21:02.440 --> 21:03.566
13.

21:03.680 --> 21:05.648
Too many.

21:05.760 --> 21:07.603
16.

